Meeting Industry Challenges with OmniStudio

The industries we serve face daunting challenges to thrive and remain competitive. To better serve customers, companies often resort to custom coding, which can be expensive, risky, can require months or years to complete. And custom projects can be delayed because a business process has changed.

Use the Applications Together

Use the OmniStudio applications together. Create guided interactions with OmniScripts; get and post data with Omnistudio Data Mappers and Integration Procedures; and display data and launch actions with Classic Cards or FlexCards.

OmniScript Basics
A Vlocity OmniScript guides users through complex processes with fast, personalized, and consistent responses.

Vlocity Cards Framework Basics
The Vlocity Cards Framework provides tools for building customer-centric, industry-specific UI components and applications on the Salesforce platform. Cards are rich in information and actions relevant to the customer's context.

Omnistudio Data Mapper or Integration Procedure?
Data Mappers read or write Salesforce SObject data or perform single-step data structure transformations. Integration Procedures can interact with many types of data, including REST APIs and Apex classes, and process it in multiple steps.

Integration Procedure Features Not in OmniScripts
Some important Integration Procedure features aren't present in OmniScripts.

Customizable Style Guide for Newport Design System
Vlocity's customers have their own set of brand guidelines and design specifications.

Omnistudio Data Mapper Basics
A Data Mapper moves Salesforce data into and out of applications. There are four types: Extract, Turbo Extract, Transform, and Load.

Vlocity User Interaction Tools
To better serve customers, companies use OmniScripts to guide users through complex processes with fast, personalized, and consistent responses.

Vlocity Data Tools
Use the OmniStudio applications together to create guided interactions, get and post data, display data, and launch actions.
